1. e4 { [%eval 0.18] } { Do the most common reply! } 1... e5 { [%eval 0.22] } 2. Nf3 $40 { [%eval 0.18] } { Develop a knight! } 2... Nf6?! $36 { [%eval 0.34] } 3. Nxe5 { [%eval 0.29] } { Now develop the other knight! } 3... Nc6?! { [%eval 1.82] } { This is where the Stafford begins! } 4. Nxc6 { [%eval 1.87] } { Take back with the d! } 4... dxc6! $132 { [%eval 1.42] } { This is where the strategy and the traps are born! } (4... bxc6!? { This weakens the pawn structure in your kingside and limits bishop movement without moving the center pawn but you can still take andvantages } 5. d3 d5 6. exd5 cxd5) 5. d3 { [%eval 1.8] } *


