1. e4 { Do the Stafford main exoskeleton! } 1... e5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. Nxe5 Nc6?! 4. Nxc6 dxc6! 5. d3 { It's time for the CRUICAL! } 5... Bc5! { Still cruical, but what if they do this? } 6. Be2 { You need abseloute dominance in the kingside, how? } 6... h5 7. O-O? Ng4 8. h3 { This position might look hard for you, it kinda is but you will see the payoff! } 8... Qd6!! (8... Nxf2?? { You will abseloutely lose your dominance over the kingside (or even the entire board honestly). } 9. Rxf2 Bxf2+ 10. Kxf2) 9. g3?? { Don't be afraid! } 9... Qxg3+!! { The pawn can't take because it's pinned! } 10. Kh1 $7 { Now it's time to mate the king! } 10... Qh2#! (10... Qxh3+?! { You can mate after this position too but you don't need to delay the mate in one. } 11. Kg1 Qh2#) *


